The paper deals with the problem of multi-object tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed approach uses Bayesian nonparametric methods, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the challenges of time-dependent cardinality and object labeling, which are related to control systems (cs.SY).
